&lt;p&gt;At Modern Animal, we’re redefining veterinary care with a technology-forward approach and an unwavering commitment to our teams. We equip our clinics with the tools, resources, and support needed to deliver exceptional care to pets and their owners. If you’re a results-driven leader ready to make a difference in a fast-growing, mission-driven organization, we’d love to meet you. Want a closer look at what makes Modern Animal different? Watch &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/@modernanimalvet&quot;&gt;Inside Modern Animal&lt;/a&gt; for a behind-the-scenes glimpse of our journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity: Area Clinic Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Area Clinic Manager, you’ll lead the operations of up to 12 clinics within your region, partnering with your Area Medical Director - as a Dyad - to drive balanced results within your region.&amp;nbsp; You and your Area Medical Director will jointly lead the Clinic Managers and Lead Doctors to ensure our teams thrive and deliver outstanding care. Reporting to the Vice President of Clinic Operations, you’ll play a key role in improving our company-level fundamentals across medical quality training, team development, member experience and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a leader who can balance strategic thinking with hands-on leadership. You’ll spend 90% of your time in clinics across your region, with occasional travel to other markets. Nights and weekends may be required to support your teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;People Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support, mentor, and develop Clinic Managers and other leaders to ensure a high-performing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with veterinarians and medical leaders to maintain the highest standards of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a communication bridge between clinics and the broader organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead talent planning to create a pipeline of future leaders and ensure clinics are staffed with top talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Operational Excellence + Balanced Results&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent, reproducible results across our 4 commitments: Medical Quality, Team Engagement, Member Experience and Profitable Growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive leading performance indicators across your leadership teams, with mastery of productive schedules, comprehensive care and a culture of development and coaching.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee your regions’ scheduling and staffing strategy to maximize efficiency and utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive performance by focusing on key inputs that impact clinic success, including membership growth and appointment optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own P&amp;amp;L accountability for your clinics, ensuring financial goals are met or exceeded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless implementation of new processes, systems, and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Clinic Growth &amp;amp; New Openings&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support end-to-end clinic openings, from staffing to operational readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on clinic-specific growth strategies, balancing member acquisition and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Doctor Hiring &amp;amp; Engagement&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a culture of pipeline building and reputation management at the clinic and regional level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure clinic teams are engaged in recruiting and sourcing strategies, inclusive of relief doctors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively source doctor candidates and ensure high quality sourcing and candidate experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure effective doctor onboarding into clinics, inclusive of relief doctors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate, Marketing will support the execution of Modern Animal’s lifecycle and retention strategies across CRM, review platforms, and broader retention initiatives. This role is responsible for bringing strategy to life, owning day-to-day execution across email/SMS, review management, member experience initiatives, and reporting. This is an ideal role for someone highly detail-oriented, organized, and eager to grow within lifecycle marketing and member experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lifecycle &amp;amp; CRM Execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute email, SMS, and push campaigns across the member lifecycle (onboarding, engagement, retention)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and QA campaigns within CRM platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support journey optimization through testing and iteration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reviews &amp;amp; Reputation Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support strategy and execution of Google and Yelp review programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor review trends and assist in surfacing insights to inform clinic-level improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally to ensure timely responses and escalation tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Member Experience Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in building and maintaining monthly reporting (NPS, app ratings, third-party reviews, churn drivers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify trends and flag outliers across clinics and regions while proposing strategies to tackle the issues they uncover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-Functional Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Operations, Technology, and Care teams to support member experience initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with ad hoc marketing strategy projects as business needs evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in marketing, CRM, lifecycle, or customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to manage multiple workstreams simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working with data; able to pull insights and spot trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM tools (e.g., Braze, Iterable, HubSpot) is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The pay range for this position is listed below; however, base pay offered may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. A sign-on bonus and equity grant units may be provided as part of the compensation package, in addition to a full range of medical, financial, and/or other benefits, dependent on the position offered. This information is provided per the California Pay Transparency Act. Base pay information is based on geographic location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$69,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$90,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We believe an equitable and inclusive work environment and a diverse, empowered team are key to achieving our mission. We’re not looking for candidates who are “culture fits.” We’re looking for candidates who can expand our culture and challenge business as usual. We strive to foster an environment where all staff can bring their whole selves to work, by their own definition, and we strive to provide all candidates with an equitable and accessible recruitm

