&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Head of Growth will own Modern Animal’s acquisition engine and be accountable for efficiently driving new member growth at scale. This role oversees a seven-figure marketing budget, defines channel strategy, and ensures investments deliver against CAC and volume targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly analytical, business-critical role with end-to-end ownership of growth performance. You will operate as the central decision-maker across channel mix, budget allocation, and performance strategy, partnering closely with Creative, Lifecycle, Analytics, and Operations to align growth with market demand and clinic capacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While initially an individual contributor, this role will manage external agencies and build the foundation for a high-performing growth team, with plans to hire an internal team in the near term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Performance&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own acquisition strategy across all paid and performance channels (e.g., Google, Meta, Yelp, Direct Mail, OOH, emerging platforms)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive channel mix and investment decisions to hit new member and CAC targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously identify opportunities to scale, reallocate, or optimize spend based on performance and business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure growth efforts are aligned with regional dynamics, clinic capacity, and expansion priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own budget planning, pacing, and forecasting across daily, monthly, and quarterly horizons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Marketing leadership to guide investment decisions and tradeoffs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage external media buying agencies (Google, Meta), holding them accountable to performance, testing velocity, and reporting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Measurement, Insights &amp;amp; Optimization&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and monitor core growth KPIs (CAC, CVR, CPL, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Analytics to understand attribution, channel incrementality, and performance drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface actionable insights and recommendations to leadership regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously test and optimize across audiences, creative, landing experiences, and channel mix&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Creative Testing Strategy&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the paid media creative strategy and testing roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Creative to develop high-performing, channel-specific assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate performance data into clear testing hypotheses and creative direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a consistent cadence of experimentation to drive incremental gains&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6-10+ years of experience in growth marketing or paid media, ideally in a high-growth, multi-location or consumer services business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience owning and optimizing seven figure paid media budgets and forecasts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep hands-on knowledge of Google Ads and Meta Ads, including strategy, testing, and performance analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and scaling acquisition across multiple channels and geographies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with the ability to translate data into clear decisions and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing agency partners and holding them accountable to performance outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with attribution models, incrementality testing, and performance measurement challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot

